Total: 48   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The purpose of this deck is simple - Burrow your creatures, get something into play to allow them to attack, then CRUSH! your opponant. Repeat as needed.<br>
<br>
Stalag starts off first.. His ability is decent by it&#39;s own.. adding 1 to a defending creature when it&#39;s attacked.. but inside a Burrow deck, he starts to shine. Effectivly, he halves the damage any of your creatures would take when attacked. Combine him with a Cave Rudwot, or a pair of Tunneler&#39;s Boots, and your set.<br>
<br>
Trygar comes next, bringing a Bwisp, &#39;fuf, and another pair of Boots. Either save a Burrow spell for the Bwisp, or wait until you can get a Tunnel Hyren out.. in either case, you&#39;d need an Arboll to pump it up to a survivable level.<br>
<br>
Gogor is this deck&#39;s last stand. His power, Gravel Storm, will do a die-roll&#39;s worth of damage to every creature, excluding those that are burrowed. Have fun!<br>
<br>
Select Cards - <br>
Hidden Door is used to grab a couple Underneath relics from your deck, usually a pair of Boots and some Goggles to go with them.<br>
<br>
Aglow is useful if your Goggles have been destroyed. Usually, with a force of Burrowed creatures, one attack is all you&#39;ll need.<br>
<br>
Burrow is in there for your Hyrens, since their ability does not cover themselves. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
